Brazil&#8217;s Olympic champion Walace has joined Bundesliga strugglers Hamburg in a deal valued by German media on Tuesday at nine million euros.&#8220;Walace is a robust and strong player. We are delighted he&#8217;s able to start playing for us straight away,&#8221; Hamburg sporting director Jens Todt said.The 21-year-old who moves from Brazilian side Gremio Porto Alegre has signed a contract until 2021.&#8220;I have to adapt quickly to my new situation,&#8221; said the defender who helped Brazil win gold at the Rio 2016 Games.&#8220;I hope to be able to help the club in the difficult position they are currently facing,&#8221; added Walace with his new side one off the bottom of the league with 13 points from 18 games.-AFP